name: bathymetric-measurements-of-little-holland-tract-sacramento-san-joaquin-delta-california-2015
notes: Bathymetric data were collected by the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) in 2015 for the Little Holland Tract in the Sacramento-San Joaquin River Delta, California. The data were collected using a personal watercraft (PWC) platform that consisted of Trimble R7 Global Navigation Satellite System (GNSS) receivers with Zephyr 2 antennas, combined with Odom Echotrac CV-100 single-beam echosounders and 200 kHz transducers. The .shp and .txt data files are available for download at http://dx.doi.org/10.5066/F7RX9954.
